ther of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert De Grendon was born about 1210, in Grendon, Warwickshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Richard de Grendon, was 41 and his mother, Mrs Margaret Grendon, was 31. He had at least 1 son with Avice De Brae."},"et":{"Abt 1210–":"umbes 1210–Surnud","1164–Male":"1164–Surnud","1210–Male":"1210–Surnud","1215–Female":"1215–Surnud","1200–1272":"1200–1272","1170–Male":"1170–Surnud","1180–Female":"1180–Surnud","1215":"1215","Abt 1210":"umbes 1210","1200":"1200","1210":"1210","1164":"1164","1272":"1272","1170":"1170","1180":"1180","Grendon, Atherstone, Warwickshire, England":"Grendon, Warwickshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1210–":"noin 1210–Kuollut","1164–Male":"1164–Kuollut","1210–Male":"1210–Kuollut","1215–Female":"1215–Kuollut","1200–1272":"1200–1272","1170–Male":"1170–Kuollut","1180–Female":"1180–Kuollut","1215":"1215","Abt 1210":"noin 1210","1200":"1200","1210":"1210","1164":"1164","1272":"1272","1170":"1170","1180":"1180","Grendon, Atherstone, Warwickshire, England":"Grendon, Warwickshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1210–":"environ 1210–Décédé","1164–Male":"1164–Décédé","1210–Male":"1210–Décédé","1215–Female":"1215–Décédée","1200–1272":"1200–1272","1170–Male":"1170–Décédé","1180–Female":"1180–Décédée","1215":"1215","Abt 1210":"environ 1210","1200":"1200","1210":"1210","1164":"1164","1272":"1272","1170":"1170","1180":"1180","Grendon, Atherstone, Warwickshire, England":"Grendon, Warwickshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Robert De Grendon est né environ 121